    {
      "tweet_id": "2050614136313164101",
      "account_handle": "Sonderling47",
      "account_id": "1899633961401229312",
      "posted_at": "2026-05-02T16:31:23.000Z",
      "first_captured_at": "2026-05-19T19:39:39.715Z",
      "last_seen_at": "2026-05-19T19:39:39.715Z",
      "deletion_detected_at": null,
      "tweet_url": "https://x.com/Sonderling47/status/2050614136313164101",
      "tweet_type": "quote",
      "reply_to_tweet_id": null,
      "reply_to_account": null,
      "quoted_tweet_id": "2050549052815585743",
      "retweeted_tweet_id": null,
      "text": "I’ve spoken with the @SpiritAirlines CEO, union leaders of flight attendants and pilots, and @USDOT to coordinate support for impacted workers.  \n \nThe Department of Labor is taking ACTION to support affected workers and help them get back to work quickly.  From immediate unemployment support to job placement and retraining, here’s what @USDOL is doing for displaced workers now:  \n \n𝗥𝗔𝗣𝗜𝗗 𝗥𝗘𝗦𝗣𝗢𝗡𝗦𝗘\n\nWe’re working to ensure fast processing, so Americans aren’t left waiting. The Department of Labor is deploying Rapid Response teams to affected hubs to help workers:  \n- File Unemployment Insurance claims  \n- Get eligibility guidance  \n- Access benefits as quickly as possible  \n \n𝗝𝗢𝗕 𝗣𝗟𝗔𝗖𝗘𝗠𝗘𝗡𝗧  \n\nOur goal is to get workers back into good-paying jobs fast! We’re connecting Spirit employees directly to new opportunities by:  \n- Coordinating with major airlines and aviation employers  \n- Hosting targeted job fairs and recruitment events  \n- Prioritizing placement through American Job Centers  \n \n𝗧𝗥𝗔𝗜𝗡𝗜𝗡𝗚 𝗔𝗡𝗗 𝗥𝗘𝗦𝗞𝗜𝗟𝗟𝗜𝗡𝗚\n\nWorkers shouldn’t have to start over. We’re activating workforce funding to support:  \n- Short-term certifications in aviation, logistics, and high-demand fields  \n- On-the-job training programs with employers  \n- Career pathways that build on existing skills \n \nWe’re also helping workers access health coverage resources, childcare and support services, and career counseling. Visit here to learn more: https://t.co/emnohU0ksG  \n \nThis is about getting Americans back on their feet quickly. @USDOL will use every tool available to connect impacted workers to jobs, training, and real opportunities.",
      "text_resolved": "I’ve spoken with the @SpiritAirlines CEO, union leaders of flight attendants and pilots, and @USDOT to coordinate support for impacted workers.  \n \nThe Department of Labor is taking ACTION to support affected workers and help them get back to work quickly.  From immediate unemployment support to job placement and retraining, here’s what @USDOL is doing for displaced workers now:  \n \n𝗥𝗔𝗣𝗜𝗗 𝗥𝗘𝗦𝗣𝗢𝗡𝗦𝗘\n\nWe’re working to ensure fast processing, so Americans aren’t left waiting. The Department of Labor is deploying Rapid Response teams to affected hubs to help workers:  \n- File Unemployment Insurance claims  \n- Get eligibility guidance  \n- Access benefits as quickly as possible  \n \n𝗝𝗢𝗕 𝗣𝗟𝗔𝗖𝗘𝗠𝗘𝗡𝗧  \n\nOur goal is to get workers back into good-paying jobs fast! We’re connecting Spirit employees directly to new opportunities by:  \n- Coordinating with major airlines and aviation employers  \n- Hosting targeted job fairs and recruitment events  \n- Prioritizing placement through American Job Centers  \n \n𝗧𝗥𝗔𝗜𝗡𝗜𝗡𝗚 𝗔𝗡𝗗 𝗥𝗘𝗦𝗞𝗜𝗟𝗟𝗜𝗡𝗚\n\nWorkers shouldn’t have to start over. We’re activating workforce funding to support:  \n- Short-term certifications in aviation, logistics, and high-demand fields  \n- On-the-job training programs with employers  \n- Career pathways that build on existing skills \n \nWe’re also helping workers access health coverage resources, childcare and support services, and career counseling. Visit here to learn more: https://www.dol.gov/agencies/eta/layoffs  \n \nThis is about getting Americans back on their feet quickly. @USDOL will use every tool available to connect impacted workers to jobs, training, and real opportunities.",
      "lang": "en",
